od, I will. I can\x{2019}t let future interfere with the hardest, most complete work of my life. I simply can\x{2019}t. Always I have been weak. Vacillating and miserable. I wish I wouldn\x{2019}t. I wish I weren\x{2019}t. I\x{2019}m so lazy, so damned lazy. This year though I have made up for last year\x{2019}s lay off. I really have batted out a lot of words. I would go through until winter if I could. But if I don\x{2019}t lay off it will be done, and if I do lay off I\x{2019}ll lose the thread. I am simply incapable of working any way but hard and fast. That is the only way I can make it. This is too bad. It is almost impossible in fact but I must get calm and quieted before I can go on. I mean that streak yesterday was curiously indecent. I don\x{2019}t know why but it was. So many things. How impossible it is for me to think. Just writing words, but the thing is starting in my brain. I must get the tempo.",
